Peters first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]], one of ten CDPS ([[Acampo, California|Acampo]], [[Collierville, California|Collierville]], [[Dogtown, San Joaquin County, California|Dogtown]], [[Mountain House, California|Mountain House]], Peters, [[Terminous, California|Terminous]], [[Thornton, California|Thornton]], [[Victor, California|Victor]], [[Waterloo, California|Waterloo]], and [[Woodbridge, California|Woodbridge]]) formed out of the deleted [[North Woodbridge, California|North Woodbridge CDP]] and [[South Woodbridge, California|South Woodbridge CDP]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Peters had a population of 708. The population density was {{convert|280.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Peters was 490 (69.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 18 (2.5%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 16 (2.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 77 (10.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 107 (15.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 182 persons (25.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Peters CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0656798 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 240 households, out of which 77 (32.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 161 (67.1%) were married-couple households, 6 (2.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 27 (11.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 46 (19.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 48 households (20.0%) were one person, and 19 (7.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.95.<ref name=DP1/> There were 184 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (76.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Peters CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0656798 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 142 people (20.1%) under the age of 18, 61 people (8.6%) aged 18 to 24, 155 people (21.9%) aged 25 to 44, 206 people (29.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 144 people (20.3%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 44.5{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 93.4 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 245 housing units at an average density of {{convert|97.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 240 (98.0%) were occupied. Of these, 184 (76.7%) were owner-occupied, and 56 (23.3%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

